[{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/assertj/assertj/issues/comments/154539080","html_url":"https://github.com/assertj/assertj/issues/518#issuecomment-154539080","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/assertj/assertj/issues/518","id":154539080,"node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDE1NDUzOTA4MA==","user":{"login":"joel-costigliola","id":382613,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM4MjYxMw==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/382613?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/joel-costigliola","html_url":"https://github.com/joel-costigliola","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joel-costigliola/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joel-costigliola/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joel-costigliola/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joel-costigliola/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joel-costigliola/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joel-costigliola/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joel-costigliola/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joel-costigliola/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joel-costigliola/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2015-11-06T21:04:30Z","updated_at":"2015-11-06T21:08:33Z","body":"Single element collection assertion would be a nice thing to have indeed !\nUnfortunately I see two problems : \n- assertj-core does not have dependencies, thus guava is not available \n- even if Guava was available, I think it is too much work to get the unique element assertion started\n\nIdeally I would have something like:\n\n``` java\nCollection<String> results = /*...*/;\nassertThat(results).uniqueElement().startsWith(\"foo\");\n```\n\nWhich is possible but can only return Object assertion, not very useful ... :crying_cat_face:\n\nOther possible approaches \n\nWhat about these other Java 8 only approaches:\n\nOption 1 : use a `Predicate`\n\n``` java\nassertThat(jedis).hasOnlyOneElementMatching(jedi -> jedi.name.equals(\"Yo! da\"), \"check name\");\n// with default check description == given\nassertThat(jedis).hasOnlyOneElementMatching(jedi -> jedi.name.equals(\"Yo! da\"));\n```\n\nThe first assertion fails with the following error message\n\n```\nExpecting:\n  <Jedi[id=1, name='Yoda', age=800]>\nto match \"check name\" predicate.\n```\n\nThe second fails too with `given` replacing `\"check name\"` in the error message.\n\nOption 2 : use a `Consumer` to let user use `assertThat` in the lambda\n\n``` java\nassertThat(jedis).hasOnlyOneElementSatisfying(jedi ->  {\n      assertThat(jedi.name).isEqualTo(\"Yoda\");\n      assertThat(jedi.age).isEqualTo(800);\n    });\n```\n\nIn that case no check description needed as we get the failed assertion error message (if any).\n\nOption 3 : ship with both options ;-)\n\nThoughts ?\n","author_association":"MEMBER","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/assertj/assertj/issues/comments/154539080/reactions","total_count":2,"+1":2,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"joel-costigliola","id":382613,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM4MjYxMw==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/382613?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/joel-costigliola","html_url":"https://github.com/joel-costigliola","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joel-costigliola/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joel-costigliola/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joel-costigliola/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joel-costigliola/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joel-costigliola/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joel-costigliola/orgs","repos_url":"ht